From: recmeet
Subject: [PATCH] Disable onnxruntime CPU memory arena for the CPU provider

The onnxruntime CPU memory arena pools allocations across inference calls,
and on long pipelines (recmeet's full transcribe + diarize + identify chain
on a 60-min meeting) does not release memory across session boundaries.
T1A field measurements (2026-04-30) showed RSS jump 17x at the diarize ->
identify-speakers transition with VmPeak 21.3 GB vs VmRSS 10.7 GB - the
classic arena fingerprint.

DisableCpuMemArena() is session-scope; this is the only public knob in the
ONNX Runtime API. There is no global env var equivalent (verified against
onnxruntime_env_config_keys.h - only kOrtEnvAllowVirtualDevices exists).

This patch is applied via FetchContent's PATCH_COMMAND in the recmeet build
system (see recmeet's CMakeLists.txt, RECMEET_PATCH_SHERPA_ARENA option).

An upstream PR is open against k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx adding a config flag
(enable_cpu_mem_arena, default true) so this can be expressed without a
vendored patch.
---
 sherpa-onnx/csrc/session.cc | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/sherpa-onnx/csrc/session.cc b/sherpa-onnx/csrc/session.cc
--- a/sherpa-onnx/csrc/session.cc
+++ b/sherpa-onnx/csrc/session.cc
@@ -67,6 +67,7 @@ Ort::SessionOptions GetSessionOptionsImpl(

   switch (p) {
     case Provider::kCPU:
+      sess_opts.DisableCpuMemArena();
       break;  // nothing to do for the CPU provider
     case Provider::kXnnpack: {
 #if ORT_API_VERSION >= 12
